\bmng
(tararUpa \eng{farther, further}; tamarUpa \eng{farthest, furthest}). 
\bnum
\num{1} dUradalilx; dUrakekx; dUravAgi: \eng{how far did you go?} niVvu eSuTx dUra hoVgididxri? 
\num{2} bahaLa dUrakekx; tuMba dUravAgi: \eng{we didn't go far} nAvu bahaLa dUra hoVgalilalx. \eng{driven far into the ground} neladoLakekx tuMba dUra nATisi. 
\num{3} (kAlada \vi) tuMba hotutx; bahaLa hiMde yA muMde: \eng{talked far into the night} rAtirx tuMba hotitxnavarege mAtADidaru. 
\num{4} tuMba; bahaLa; hecucx; \eng{far different} tuMba vayxtAyxsaviruva. \eng{far better} hecucx utatxma. \eng{far the best} bahaLa sherxVSaThx; atuyxtatxma. 
\enum
\emng

\noindent
\gl{\pagu}
\bmng
\hypertarget{far nuga1}{} 
\hyperdef{F}{far pagu}{} 
\bnum
\numi{1} \eng{as far as} 
\banum
\alnum{a} (sathxLada \vi) alilxyavaregU. 
\alnum{b} elilxyavaregAdarU; eSuTx dUrakAkxdarU: \eng{travel as far as you like} ninage elilxyavarege iSaTxvoV alilxyavaregU parxyANa mADu. 
\alnum{c} A maTiTxge; aSaTxra maTiTxge: \eng{as far as I can} nananx keYlAda maTiTxge. 
\alnum{d} adeV dUra; aSeTxV dUra: \eng{we didn't go as far as others} nAvu uLidavaru hoVdaSuTx dUra hoVgalilalx. 
\eanum
\numie
\num{2} \eng{far forth} aSaTxravaregU. 
\num{3} \eng{from far} bahaLa dUradiMda; tuMba dUradiMda; sAkaSuTx dUradiMda. 
\numi{4} \eng{how far} 
\banum
\alnum{a} eSuTxmaTiTxge; eSaTxravarege; elilxyavarege. 
\alnum{b} eSuTx dUra. 
\hyperdef{F}{far(1) pagu(5)}{} 
\hypertarget{far nuga5}{} 
\eanum
\numie
\num{5} \eng{(in) so far as} aSuTxmaTiTxge; aSaTxramaTiTxge; alilxyavarege; adaravarege. 
\hyperdef{F}{far(1) pagu(6)}{} 
\numi{6} \eng{so far} 
\banum
\alnum{a} aSuTxdUra; alilxya -- varege, tanaka. 
\eanum
\numie
\numi{7} \eng{so far as} 
\banum
\alnum{a} = \hyperlink{far nuga1}{?pagu? \((1)\).} 
\alnum{b} = \hyperlink{far nuga5}{?pagu? \((5)\).} 
\eanum
\numie
\num{8} \eng{so far forth as} eSaTxravarege ideyoV aSaTXravaregU. 
\enum
\emng

\noindent
\gl{\nuga}
\bmng
\bnum
\numi{1} \eng{by far} 
\banum
\alnum{a} bahaLa -- hecAcxgi, adhikavAgi: \eng{expensive by far} bahaLa dubAriyAgi. 
\alnum{b} sapxSaTxvAgi; visapxSaTxvAgi; nisasxMshayavAgi: \eng{by far the best} sapxSaTxvAgiyeV atuyxtatxma. 
\hyperdef{F}{far(1)nuga(2)}{} 
\eanum
\numie
\numi{2} \eng{far and away} 
\banum
\alnum{a} atayxMta hecAcxgi; bahaLa aMtaradiMda. 
\alnum{b} nisasxMdeVhavAgi; nisasxMdigadhxvAgi: \eng{he is far and away the best player on the team} avanu nisasxMdigadhxvAgi A taMDada atuyxtatxma ATagAra. 
\eanum
\numie
\num{3} \eng{far and near} elelxDeyalilxyU; elelxlilxyU; elAlx kaDeyU; elalx sathxLadalilxyU; elelxDeyU; elAlx dikikxnalilxyU; savaRtarx: \eng{he searched for the child far and near} avanu elAlx kaDeyU maguvigAgi huDukida. 
\hyperdef{F}{far(1) nuga(4)}{} 
\num{4} \eng{far and wide} bahu dUradavarege; vishAlavAgi; vAyxpakavAgi. 
\num{5} \eng{far back} bahaLa hiMde; pArxciVnakAladalilx. 
\num{6} \eng{far be it from me to ....} (TiVkisuvudu, madheYxbAyi hAkuvudu, \mo vugaLa \vi) adu nanage iSaTxvilalx; nAnu adanunx mADalAre; naninxMda adu eMdigU Agadu. 
\numi{7} \eng{far between} 
\banum
\alnum{a} aparUpavAda; viraLavAda. 
\alnum{b} aparUpavAgi; viraLavAgi. 
\alnum{c} bahukAla biTuTx baruva; bahaLa aMtaraviruva. 
\eanum
\numie
\num{8} \eng{far from} parxtiyAgi; dUravAgi; oMdaraMte iruvudara badalu adakekx virudadhxvAgi: \eng{the problem is far from easy} samaseyx sulaBavAgilalx. \eng{far from depending himself he apologised} tananxnunx samathiRsikoLuLxva badalu avanu kaSxme koVrida. \eng{his work is far from satisfactory} avana kelasa taqpitxkaravAgilalx. 
\num{9} \eng{far from it} adakekx bahudUra; adakikxMta bahaLa beVreyAgide. 
\numi{10} \eng{go far} 
\banum
\alnum{a} (vayxkitxgaLa \vi) muMduvare; sAdhisu; yashasusx gaLisu: \eng{he is bold and will go far} avanu dhiVra, bahaLa muMduvareyutAtxne, sAdhisutAtxne. 
\alnum{b} sahAyamADu; mADalu yA neraveVrisalu neravAgu: \eng{go far to alleviate the suffering} saMkaTavanunx shamanagoLisalu neravAgi. 
\alnum{c} (haNada \vi) (saraku, seVve, \mo vanunx) koLaLxlu sAkAgu, shakatxvAgu: \eng{a rupee does not go so far today as it did ten years ago} hatutx vaSaRgaLa hiMde oMdu rUpAyi koLuLxtitxdadxSuTx iMdu koLuLxvudilalx.

\num{6} \eng{have at one's finger tips (}\engit{or} \eng{finger ends)} karatalAmalakavAgi hoMdiru; beraLina tudiyalelxV hoMdiru; cenAnxgi tiLidiru; sAvxdhiVnadalilxTuTxkoMDiru.

\hypertarget{finger nuga8}{} 
\numi{8} \eng{lay a finger on (}\engit{or} \eng{upon)} 
\banum

\alnum{b} saMbaMdhakekx, goDavege, taMTege -- baru yA hoVgu: \eng{if you dare lay a finger on him} avanige beraLu soVkisidedxV Adare; niVnu avana taMTegeVnAdarU hoVdare yA baMdare. 
\eanum
\numie
\numi{9} \eng{lay one's finger on} 
\banum
\alnum{a} KacitavAgi toVrisu; nidiRSaTxvAgi toVrisu; boTuTx mADu; beraLiTuTx toVrisu: \eng{laid his finger on the real trouble} nijavAda toMdareyanunx KacitavAgi toVrisida. 
\alnum{b} nenapige taMduko; nenapu mADiko: \eng{I know his name, but I can't lay my finger on it} avana hesaranunx balelx, Adare adanunx nenapige taMdukoLaLxlAre. 
\alnum{c} kaMDuhiDi; iruva sathxLa patetxhacucx: \eng{ I haven't been able to lay my finger on the book you wanted} niVnu bayasida pusatxka elilxdeyoV adanunx nAnu kaMDuhiDiyalAgalilalx. 
\eanum
\numie
\num{10} \eng{let slip through one's fingers} hiDita, avakAsha -- kaLeduko. 
\hypertarget{finger nuga11}{} 
\num{11} \eng{lift, move, raise a finger} beraLalugisu; beraLetutx; atayxlapx parxyatanxvanAnxdarU mADu: \eng{the house was falling into ruin, but he would not lift a finger to repair it} mane kusidu biVLutitxtutx, AdarU adanunx durasutxmADalu avanu beraLalugisalU ilalx. 
\num{12} \eng{look through one's finger at} kANadavanaMte naTisu: \eng{if the king himself should look through his fingers and wink at it} doreyeV adanunx kaMDarU kANadavanaMte naTisidare. 
\num{13} \eng{my fingers itch to do.....} adanunx mADalu nananx keY kaDiyutatxde, turisutatxde, tavakisutatxde. 
\num{14} \eng{point finger at} (\kanmu\ tirasAkxradiMda) obabxnatatx yA oMdaratatx boTuTxmADu, beraLu toVrisu. 
\num{15} \eng{put a finger on (}\engit{or} \eng{upon)} = \hyperlink{finger nuga8}{?nuga? \((8)\).}

\num{19} \eng{to the finger-nails} pUtiRyAgi; saMpUNaRvAgi. 
\hyperdef{F}{finger(1) nuga(20)}{} 
\num{20} \eng{turn (}\engit{or} \eng{twist) person round one's (little) finger} (obabxnanunx) heVgeMdare hAge ADisu; sarAgavAgi avana meVle pUNaR parxBAva biVru: \eng{she turns her husband round her little finger} avaLu tananx gaMDananunx heVgeMdare hAge ADisutAtxLe.

\bentry
\word[follow(1)]{follow}
\pron{phAloV}
\gl{\sakirx}
\bmng
\bnum
\num{1} (calisutitxruva vasutx yA vayxkitxya) hiMde hoVgu; hiMde baru; anusarisu; benunx hatutx; benunx hiDi; hiMbAlisu: \eng{they followed us for miles} avaru namamxnunx meYligaTaTxle hiMbAlisidaru. 
\num{2} (hAdi) hiDi; (dAri) hiDidu hoVgu; (mAgaRdalilx) sAgu: \eng{follow this road for a mile} oMdu meYli I dAri hiDidu hoVgu. 
\num{3} (karxmadalilx, kAladalilx) anusarisu; hiMbAlisu: \eng{follow the leader} nAyakananunx anusarisu. 
\num{4} oDagUDi hoVgu yA baru; saMgaDa hoVgu; joteyalilx hoVgu: \eng{he followed her home from the party} saMtoVSakUTavAda meVle avanu avaLa joteyalilx maneyavaregU hoVdanu. 
\num{5} seVvisu; seVvemADu: \eng{you may depend on my following him} nAnu avana seVve mADuveneMba necicxke niVnu iTuTxkoLaLxbahudu. 
\num{6} mecicx hiMbAlisu; anucaranAgi hoVgu; anuyAyiyAgi hoVgu: \eng{I have followed him these twenty years} I ipapxtutx vaSaRkAla nAnu avananunx mecicxkoMDu hiMbAlisidedxVne. 
\num{7} anusarisu; (oMdara) PalavAgi baru; pariNAmavAgi baru; oLagoLuLx: \eng{trade follows the flag} vAyxpAra bAvuTavanunx anusarisutatxde; bAvuTa hoVda kaDe (adara pariNAmavAgi) vAyxpAra hoVgutatxde. \eng{because he is good it does not follow that he is wise} avanu oLeLxyavaneMba kAraNadiMda, avanu viveVki eMdu Palisuvudilalx (heVLalAguvudilalx). 
\num{8} sAdhisalu yatinxsu; guriyalilxTuTxko: \eng{to follow knowledge} jAcnxnavanunx sAdhisalu. 
\num{9} mAgaRdashaRkananAnxgi BAvisu; nAyakananAnxgi maninxsu; sAvxmiyAgi aMgiVkarisu: \eng{the Indians followed Nehru} BAratiVyaru neharUravaranunx nAyakananAnxgi aMgiVkarisidaru. 
\num{10} heVLidaMte mADu; vidheVyanAgi naDeduko; pAlisu: \eng{follow orders} AjecnxgaLanunx pAlisu. 
\num{11} (aBipArxyagaLanunx, dheyxVyavanunx) hiDi; anusarisu; avalaMbisu; aMgiVkarisu: \eng{follow a policy of peace} shAMtiniVtiyanunx anusarisu. 
\num{12} -aMte mADu ; -hAge naDe; -aMte naDeduko; anusarisu; AdashaRvAgi tegeduko; opipxko: \eng{follow his example} avana meVlapxMkitxyanunx anusarisu; avana AdashaRdaMte naDe. 
\num{13} (vaqtitx \mo vanunx) hiDi; avalaMbisu: \eng{he followed the profession of an artist} avanu kalAvida vaqtitxyanunx avalaMbisidanu. 
\num{14} (vAdavanunx, BASaNakAranu heVLuvudanunx) athaRmADiko; tiLiduko; garxhisu: \eng{the argument is too difficult for them to follow} A vAdavu avarige athaRmADikoLaLxlAgadaSuTx kaSaTxvAgide. 
\num{15} (vayxkitxya yA vasutxvina) hiMde hoVgu; hiMde bA; hiMbAlisu: \eng{follow in his steps} avana hejejx hiDidu hoVgu. 
\num{16} shavayAterxyalilx BAgavahisu; shavada hiMde yA joteyalilx samxshAnadavarege hoVgu; obabx vayxkitxya shavasaMsAkxrakekx hoVgu. 
\num{17} (GaTanegaLu, kAlecxMDATada taMDa \mo vugaLa bagegx) ititxVcina sithxtiyanunx yA parxgatiyanunx tiLidiru. 
\num{18} taruvAyadadxnunx odagisu, niVDu; taruvAya baruvaMte, AguvaMte mADu: \eng{follow angry words with blows} koVpada nuDigaLa taruvAya ETu koDu. 
\enum
\emng

\noindent
\gl{\akirx}
\bmng
\bnum
\num{1} hiMde hoVgu; hiMde baru: \eng{if one sheep goes through the gate the rest will follow} oMdu kuri geVTina mUlaka nugigxdare uLidavU adara hiMde hoVgutatxve. \eng{follow in one's steps} obabxnanunx anusarisu, hiMbAlisu; obabxna hejejx hiDidu hoVgu. \eng{follow in the wake of} oMdara hAdiyanunx anusarisi hoVgu, baru. 
\num{2} taruvAya baru; AmeVle baru; muMde baru: \eng{letter follows} kAgada taruvAya barutatxde. 
\num{3} saMgaDaviru; joteyalilxru. 
\num{4} seVvisu; seVvemADu. 
\num{5} (pariNAmavAgi) uMTAgu; saMBavisu; Palisu; anugatavAgu; sididhxsu: \eng{that he must be innocent follows from this} avanu niraparAdhiyAgirabeVkeMdu idariMda sidadhxvAgutatxde. \eng{it must follow as the night follows the day} hagalAda meVle rAtirxyAguvaMteyeV adu sididhxsutatxde. 
\num{6} (karxmadalilx) taruvAya baru; AmeVle baru; anukarxmavAgi baru: \eng{his arguments are as follows} avana vAdagaLu karxmavAgi hiVgive. 
\num{7} AmeVle Agu; taruvAya saMBavisu: \eng{after the defeat disorders followed} soVlina taruvAya galaBegaLu Aduvu. 
\enum
\emng

\noindent
\gl{\pagu}
\bmng
\bnum
\num{1} \eng{as follows} I keLaginaMte; I muMdinadaraMte; hiVge. 
\numi{2} \eng{follow after} 
\banum
\alnum{a} sAdhisalu sharxmisu; paDeyalu sharxmisu. 
\alnum{b} benanxTuTx: hiMbAlisu. 
\eanum
\numie
\num{3} \eng{follow on} (kirxkeTf) (boVliMgf edurisuva pakaSxda saradi biTuTx) maraLi bAyxTina ATa muMduvarisu; (edurALigiMta nidiRSaTx saMKeyxya OTagaLanunx kaDame gaLisidadxriMda) matetx bAyxTu mADu; edurupakaSxvanunx bAyxTu mADalu iLisalAgade tAneV matetx bAyxTu mADalu pArxraMBisu. 
\numi{4} \eng{follow out} 
\banum
\alnum{a} kaDeyavaregU sAdhisu; konemuTiTxsu; kaDegANisu. 
\alnum{b} (sUcanegaLu \mo vanunx) yathAvatAtxgi kAyaRrUpakekx taru; karAruvAkAkxgi pAlisu. 
\eanum
\numie
\num{5} \eng{follow suit} aMteyeV, hAgeyeV mADu; matotxbabx mADidaMte mADu: \eng{the little girl jumped over the fence, and her playmates followed suit} cikakx huDugi A beVliyanunx hAridaLu, avaLa ATada jotegAtiyarU hAgeyeV mADidaru. 
\num{6} \eng{follow the sea} nAvikanAgu. 
\numi{7} \eng{follow through} 
\banum
\alnum{a} gAlfphx \mo\ ATagaLalilx ceMDanunx hoDeda naMtara dAMDina biVsanunx sAdhayxvAdaSuTx muMduvarisu. 
\alnum{b} oMdu kelasavanunx -- mugisu; pUNaRgoLisu; konegoLisuvavarege mADu.

\eanum
\numie
\numi{8} \eng{follow up} 
\banum
\alnum{a} biDade anusarisu; benanxTiTx; anudhAvisu. 
\alnum{b} (hiMdina ETu \mo vakekx) matotxMdu ETu hAku; punaH ETu koDu. 
\alnum{c} (kAlecxMDATa \mo valilx) beMbalakoDalu ceMDina (ATagArana) hatitxraviru. 
\alnum{d} taniKeyanunx muMduvaresu; inunx hecicxna taniKe -- keYgoLuLx, pArxraMBisu. 
\eanum
\numie
\enum
\emng
